
[1]evocation

   EVOCA'TION, n. A calling forth; a calling or bringing from

   concealment.

   1. A calling from one tribunal to another.

   2. Among the Romans, a calling on the gods of a besieged city to
   forsake it and come over to the besiegers; a religious ceremony of
   besieging armies.
